cs.CR, cs.SI, cs.CY, cs.NI, cs.DS 

This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Science sub-category of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) as it deals with internet security and abuse data generation process. It could also belong to cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) as it discusses the heterogeneity in size and business models of hosting providers. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.CY (Computers and Society) as it discusses the implications of premature inferences from raw abuse indicators on security efforts of actors. It could also be classified under cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) as it deals with hosting networks and their associated abuse. Finally, it could belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) as it uses statistical models to estimate key parameters of the abuse data generation process.
